      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MAGICAL MOMENTS (4) assumed the unfamiliar role of leader and proceeded to thrash a BM64 field over this course and distance last start. In a race that lacks obvious pace she may attempt a similar feat this afternoon. Enjoys racing here so stick with her. AUDENZIA (2) backs up four days after a comfortable victory over 1450m on the opening of the Grange circuit. In the money at six of eight runs over today's course and distance. Key runner again on the quick turnaround. SONOFDEC (1) worked home well for third when resuming over 1250m at Canterbury recently. Prefers it wet but he is the class runner of the field and looks to be back in good shape. GO GLENN (5) overcame some interference to record a game first-up win over 1200m at Gosford last start. An extra 200m on a roomier track is the perfect second-up scenario. MOGWAI (3) has won two from four at Kembla. Gets a pass-mark for his first-up effort at Canterbury. Cannot be ruled out.",
